<HEADLINE>
<P>
POPE NAMES NEW BISHOP OF GUADALAJARA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pope John Paul II named a new archbishop for Guadalajara, Mexico, on Thursday, 
nearly a year after the city's Roman Catholic leader was killed in an airport 
shootout. 
</P>
<P>
 Msgr. Juan Sandoval Iniguez, 61, the city's new archbishop, had been bishop of 
Ciudad Juarez, Mexico, since July, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The Guadalajara post has been vacant since May 24, 1993, when Cardinal Juan 
Jesus Posadas Ocampo was killed in a drug cartel-related shootout at 
Guadalajara's airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
