'SEX AND SIN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In response to "Sex and Sin: There Is a Difference," by Rabbi Michael Gotlieb, 
Commentary, April 14: 
</P>
<P>
 How can Rabbi Gotlieb preach the morality of premarital sex without mentioning 
the millions of children (and immortal souls) thus created? The possibility for 
creating children without two committed parents makes the act immoral. How can 
Gotlieb admit that "premarital sex is unholy," yet require our public schools 
to teach our children how to engage in this unholiness without risk? 
</P>
