</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CERRITOS CENTER LAUDED FOR DESIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cerritos Center for the Performing Arts and architects Barton Myers 
Associates have won raves from two organizations recognizing the center for its 
architectural design. 
</P>
<P>
 The center was one of five theaters nationwide to receive a 1994 Honor Award 
for excellence from the United States Institute of Theater Technology, which 
hailed it as "the most sophisticated project we've seen in terms of 
architecture, technology and urban design." 
</P>
<P>
 The center also won the 1994 Kaufman and Broad Award from the Los Angeles 
Business Council earlier this month. The award, granted to two public 
facilities annually, recognizes the center's aesthetics. 
</P>
