<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; RELAY VICTORY HELPS EL TORO UPSET CAPISTRANO VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Colin Lavin anchored the winning mile relay team to give El Toro a 69-67 upset 
victory over first-place Capistrano Valley in South Coast League boys' track 
and field Thursday at El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers trailed Capistrano Valley, 67-64, going into the mile relay. 
</P>
<P>
 Travis Harr played a key role for El Toro, winning the 110 hurdles in 16.3 and 
the 300 hurdles in 40.6. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 80, Canyon 56 -- Troy Langley of Canyon jumped 6-10 1/4, the best 
high jump in the county this season. His jump also set a Canyon record. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 74, Sunny Hills 53 -- Mark Gonzalez won the 100 (11.1), 200 (23.0) and 
triple jump (38-5) for Sonora (5-1, 3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 101, Laguna Beach 16 -- Jesse McDonald set the school record in 
the discus (168-8 1/2) for Laguna Hills (6-1, 4-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 82, Newport Harbor 53 -- Tony Muniz won the high jump (6-0), long 
jump (22-0 1/2) and triple jump (45-2) for Woodbridge (6-0, 6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 102, Servite 34 -- Aron Bergman ran personal bests in the 100 meters 
(11.2) and 200 meters for Marina. The Vikings remain undefeated with a 7-0, 6-0 
record. 
</P>
<P>
 In Century League girls' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 77, Foothill 50 -- Kim Nelson won the 800 (2:30.3), 1,600 (5:44.1) and 
Nelson, Megan Gillespie and Allison Bunton tied for first in the 3,200 (13:00) 
to lead Canyon (4-0, 4-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 95, Cypress 27 -- Stacy Wright won the high jump (4-8), long jump 
(15-6), triple jump (33-0) and placed second in the 100 hurdles for Katella 
(5-2, 3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 94, Fullerton 32 -- Emily Keeler won the 100 (12.3), 220 (27.3), the 
triple jump (33-1) and ran the anchor leg of the winning 440 relay (54.1) for 
Troy. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 84, Kennedy 39 -- Jaime Jenks won the 800 (2:56.8), 1,600 
(6:23.6) and the 3,200 (13:56) for undefeated Bolsa Grande (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 102, Western 24 -- Sophomore Sommer Bomgaars jumped a personal 
best 5-0 in the high jump for Brea-Olinda. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 104, Laguna Beach 14 -- Tiffany Boykin set the school record in 
the 200 (27.4) and Amy Colton set the school record in the discus (104-0 1/2) 
to lead Laguna Hills (5-3, 4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 84, Irvine 37 -- Heather Novak won the 100 hurdles (16.2), 
long jump (17-2) and triple jump (35-4) to lead Santa Margarita (6-0, 6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 110, Rosary 17 -- Jenny Benson ran a personal best in the 200 meters 
(27.1) and equaled her personal best in the 100 meters (13.0) for Marina (5-2, 
4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 South Coast League gymnastics: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 165.4, Dana Hills 41.6 -- Joslin Gemsch won the all-around 
for the Cougars (9-0, 5-0), with a score of 31.4. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange League golf: 
</P>
<P>
 Western 185, Magnolia 222 -- Tiger Woods shot a three-under 32 for Western 
(10-4, 5-2) at Dad Miller. Included in his round was an eagle on the par-four 
12th hole. 
</P>
