<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; NASTER PITCHES NO-HITTER FOR MOORPARK, 8-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Naster pitched a no-hitter in Moorpark College's 8-0 victory over Oxnard 
in a Western State Conference game Thursday at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Naster, a sophomore right-hander from Thousand Oaks High, took a perfect game 
into the sixth inning before issuing one of his three walks. He struck out 
five. 
</P>
<P>
 The no-hitter was saved in the seventh by shortstop Ryan Briggs, who made a 
nice play on a ground ball behind second base. Briggs also had three hits and 
four runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 Naster (7-2) pitched for the 1992 Newbury Oaks American Legion team, pitching 
a shutout in the World Series final. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Nykoluk hit his fifth home run to highlight a six-run second inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Wayne Northern added two doubles for the Raiders (16-14-2, 9-7-1 in conference 
play). 
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield 17, Glendale 7 -- The Vaqueros (10-18-1, 8-10-1) walked 19 batters 
and hit four, leading to 10 runs in a WSC game at Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Ed Gillis led Bakersfield with three hits and two RBIs. Nate Baez, Rob Turner 
and Randy Vickers had two hits apiece for Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica 5, Pierce 2 -- Robert Brennan scattered seven hits as Santa 
Monica upset Pierce in a WSC game. Robert Cox of Santa Monica hit a two-run 
home run in the sixth inning to break open a scoreless game. After Pierce 
scored one run in the seventh, Santa Monica responded with three runs in the 
eighth. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss dropped Pierce into a first place tie with Bakersfield with 12-7 
conference records. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 13, Canyons 11 -- Will Skett was four for five with a home run, three 
RBIs and four runs, leading the Monarchs (12-16-1, 10-9) in a WSC game at 
Valencia. Skett has hit safely in 10 of 13 at-bats. 
</P>
<P>
 Ozzie Areu was three for three with three RBIs for Valley. Jorge Dorado's 
two-run single in the fifth inning capped Valley's comeback from an 8-2 
deficit. Kevin Szymanski picked up the victory and Juan Velazquez recorded his 
first save. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 9, Mt. San Jacinto 3 -- Eric Cole was two for three with a run 
and an RBI, leading the Marauders (13-14, 7-11) in a Foothill Conference game 
at Hemet. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Cox homered and Will Wallace had two RBIs. Earlier, the Marauders played 
the final three innings of a 21-10 victory against Mt. San Jacinto. That game 
was suspended March 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Biola 5, The Master's 0 -- Brian Schmidt pitched a complete game for Biola in 
a NAIA District III game at La Mirada. Curtis Marsh broke open a scoreless game 
in the sixth inning with a run-scoring single. 
