<HEADLINE>
<P>
ESPERANZA'S KIERULFF POSTS HIGH JUMP BEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esperanza junior Kristy Kierulff cleared 5 feet 10 3/4 in the high jump, the 
best mark for a high school girl in the nation this season, as Esperanza beat 
Los Alamitos, 84-37, in an Empire League track and field meet. 
</P>
<P>
 Kierulff won the State championship as a freshman with a jump of 5-10. She has 
cleared 5-8 or higher seven times this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Kelly O'Connor won the long jump (16-10 1/2), triple jump (36-9) and 
discus (103-7) for Esperanza (4-0 in league). 
</P>
</TEXT>
