moved into a first-place tie with a 6-4 victory over host Saddleback Thursday 
in an Orange Empire Conference baseball game. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzales hit a two-run home run in the first inning and added home runs in the 
third and ninth.He also pitched the final 4 2/3 innings for the victory. He 
allowed one hit and had eight strikeouts and four walks. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (27-10) is tied for first with Riverside at 13-5.  
</P>
<P>
