<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: NEWPORT BEACH'S BALDWIN CO. APPOINTS 2 NEW DIVISION 
PRESIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael R. Engle and Louis J. Malone have been appointed division presidents 
for the Baldwin Co., a Newport Beach home builder. Engle will head the 
company's Orange County division, while Malone will run the Ventura 
division.Engle has more than 20 years' experience, most recently as senior vice 
president and division manager of Southwest Diversified/Coscan Partners. He 
also spent six years as executive vice president for the Sunnyglen Corp., a 
commercial, industrial and residential development company. Malone has headed 
his own company, Malone Homes in Tustin, since 1987. He was formerly president 
and chief operating officer of Donald Bren Co. in Newport Beach and, before 
that, executive vice president and chief financial officer of McCarthy Co. in 
Santa Ana. 
</P>
