<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SADDLEBACK/SOUTH BEACH; SOCCER PROGRAM FOR DISABLED 
CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sign-ups will be held Saturday for developmentally challenged youngsters who 
want to play soccer. 
</P>
<P>
 The American Youth Soccer Organization's VIP program will accept all children, 
regardless of handicap, providing that they are ambulatory. 
</P>
<P>
 Sign-ups will take place at Newhart Elementary School, 24001 Oso Viejo in 
Mission Viejo between 8 a.m. and 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The soccer league is tailored for children who would be overmatched on a team 
with players who are not handicapped. The score is not kept, and rules are 
simplified. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants in the VIP program have spotters who help guide them on the 
soccer field. 
</P>
<P>
 Children who live in the South County area from the El Toro Y to San Clemente 
are eligible if born before Jan. 30, 1990. Proof of age is required for all new 
players.  
</P>
<P>
 The registration fee is $55 per player with a maximum charge of $150 per 
family. A non-refundable registration fee of $15 is included. 
</P>
<P>
 Other registration days are planned. Information: (714) 859-8557. 
</P>
