<P>
NOVELIST CARLOS FUENTES TO SPEAK AT CHAPMAN UNIVERSITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One of Latin America's most renowned novelists will speak Monday at Chapman 
University, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Fuentes will speak on "The Creative Spirit as a Force for Humanism," 
Chapman spokesman Jeff Coulter said. Fuentes is known for books including "The 
Old Gringo" and "The Death of Artemio Cruz." 
</P>
<P>
 Fuentes has been named Chapman's Distinguished Writer for 1994. The 
Distinguished Writer series brings well-known authors to the Chapman campus to 
discuss their work, Coulter said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fuentes will speak in Chapman Auditorium, 333 N. Glassell St. The lecture will 
begin at 8 p.m., and admission is $7 for the general public and $3 for 
students, senior citizens and groups of 10 or more. 
</P>
