EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Food and tobacco conglomerate RJR Nabisco Holdings Co. said its net income 
rose 19.6% in the first quarter as onetime events boosted its latest results 
and depressed last year's figures.Excluding special factors, earnings were off 
8% from a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The New York-based firm reported net income of $195 million in the three 
months ended March 31, compared to $163 million a year earlier. After preferred 
dividends were paid, earnings rose to $162 million, or 12 cents a share, from 
$157 million, or 12 cents a share, in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue fell 4.5% to $3.57 billion, from $3.74 billion in 1993. 
</P>
