<DOCID> 034705 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
April 22, 1994, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
56 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CalFed Sells $231 Million in Bad Loans: The bulk sale represents about a 
quarter of the bad loans California Federal Bank said it would sell to shore up 
its balance sheet. The Los Angeles-based thrift would not identify the buyer or 
say how much it received, but it said the outstanding balances of the loans 
totaled $231 million. 
</P>
