<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: SUMNER REDSTONE, MARTIN DAVIS JOINING FORCES AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a brief separation, former Paramount Communications Inc. Chairman Martin 
Davis is reuniting with Viacom Inc. chief Sumner Redstone. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis was named Thursday to the board of Redstone's National Amusements Inc., 
the parent of Viacom, which recently bested QVC Inc. in a $10-billion takeover 
war for Paramount. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis stepped down as head of Paramount last month after Viacom gained control 
of the company. Earlier this week, he announced he was forming Wellspring 
Associates Inc. to specialize in restructuring troubled companies. 
</P>
<P>
 * Entertainment executive Myles E. Mangram has formed Black Lion Records, an 
independent label that in June will release its first album, "nita whitaker." 
</P>
<P>
 Mangram is president of the label. Other executives are Chea Rivera, vice 
president, and Sharon Thompson, label coordinator. 
</P>
<P>
 * Former Sony Pictures Entertainment Chief Financial Officer Abbott Brown has 
joined merchant banking firm Pacific yCapital Group as managing director and 
chief financial officer. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trudy Lartz has joined SoundScan as sales director. 
