<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; DOCTOR 
CONVICTED OF SEXUALLY ASSAULTING PATIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Brentwood doctor was convicted Thursday on 10 counts of sexually assaulting 
his female patients, but a jury deadlocked on eight other counts and acquitted 
the doctor on two remaining charges.  
</P>
<P>
 Superior Court Judge Charles Horan ordered Yahya Lavi, who has been free on 
bail, taken into immediate custody pending his June 6 sentencing.He faces more 
than 43 years in state prison.  
</P>
<P>
 Lavi, who works at several Los Angeles-area health clinics and has a private 
practice in Brentwood, was accused of 20 counts of drugging, raping and 
sexually assaulting five women. The jury could not agree whether Lavi had 
drugged some of the women.  
</P>
<P>
 In all, Lavi was convicted of three counts of genital penetration by a foreign 
object, three misdemeanor counts of sexual battery, two counts of sexual 
battery on an institutionalized person, and two counts of rape of an 
unconscious person. 
</P>
</TEXT>
