<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CERRITOS; RAPE SUSPECT 
ORDERED TO BE HELD WITHOUT BAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-old suspected gang member accused of raping three 12-year-old girls 
in the Cerritos area was ordered held without bail Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Wagner R. Sampang, who authorities say is a transient, was arraigned at Los 
Cerritos Municipal Court in Bellflower.He pleaded innocent to eight felony 
counts, including five charges of forcible rape and three counts of forcible 
lewd acts with a child under the age of 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Sampang is accused of befriending young girls at shopping malls and in other 
public settings, raping them and then warning them that they would face 
retaliation by members of his gang if they reported the incidents. He was 
arrested Tuesday evening as he left a friend's house in Lakewood, sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Judge Philip K. Mautino ordered Sampang held without bail. Deputy Dist. Atty. 
Robert Samoian had asked Mautino to set bail at $1 million "due to the 
predatory nature of the defendant's conduct." 
</P>
<P>
 A preliminary hearing is scheduled for May 3. 
</P>
