<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; FREEWAY ACCIDENT TAKES WOMAN'S LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 47-year-old Garden Grove woman was killed Thursday morning when she lost 
control of her car and crashed into a semitrailer truck on the Garden Grove 
Freeway, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 In Ja Nam was driving east on the freeway near the Magnolia Avenue off-ramp 
about 11:30 a.m. when she lost control of her vehicle, swerved into the next 
lane and hit the rear wheels of the truck, CHP Officer Denise Quesada said. 
</P>
<P>
 The impact forced the woman to veer to the right shoulder, Quesada said. The 
vehicle overturned and slid back onto the freeway, where it came to a stop in 
one of the middle lanes, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman was pronounced dead at the scene by paramedics, Quesada said. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck driver, Mitchell Pettyjohn, 32, of Palmdale, was not injured, she 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident closed a lane of the freeway, causing a three-mile backup for 
eastbound traffic that lasted until about 3 p.m., CHP Officer Joan Rivas said. 
FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
