ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR CLEANUP EFFORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 300 volunteers are expected to turn out Saturday to help the city with 
graffiti removal and park cleanup. 
</P>
<P>
 The effort marks the city's participation in the nationwide "Volunteer 
Connection Day."The national effort focuses on urging people of all ages to do 
volunteer work for their communities. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers will meet at 8 a.m. at the Garden Grove Municipal Services Center, 
13802 Newhope St. "They will then get their assignments in various areas and go 
to those assignments to work until noon," said Mike Adams, administrative 
analyst with the city's Public Services Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The anticipated volunteers are from civic groups and youth organizations that 
have done volunteer work for the city, Adams said. He said, however, that any 
individual may help on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Those wishing to help should call (714) 741-5375 before Saturday to get on the 
assignment list, Adams said. 
</P>
<P>
 The effort is also part of a countywide program coordinated by the Volunteer 
Center of Greater Orange County. BILL BILLITER 
