<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER REPORTS ATTEMPT TO KIDNAP 2-YEAR-OLD CHILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are investigating a possible attempted kidnaping Thursday 
of a 2-year-old child in front of a shopping center in the 22300 block of El 
Toro Road. 
</P>
<P>
 A South County woman was walking to her car about 12:30 p.m., with her child, 
groceries and rented videotapes, according to sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini, when 
another woman approached, bumped the mother and attempted to snatch her child. 
</P>
<P>
 "The mother grabbed the child's clothing and there was a short struggle," and 
the mother pulled her child back, Martini said. The assailant ran off, got into 
a car driven by a second person and fled. Officers would not identify the 
mother. 
</P>
<P>
 "Both victims are in good condition," Martini said.  
</P>
<P>
 "You really have to commend the action of the mother. She fought for her child 
and won." 
</P>
<P>
 The woman returned to the video store, where a clerk called police. 
</P>
<P>
 In the struggle, some of the mother's personal property disappeared, and 
Martini said that the assault could have been a diversion for a robbery. 
</P>
<P>
 Nonetheless, he said, "we are looking at it as an attempted kidnaping. . . . 
It's a warning flag for everyone." 
</P>
</TEXT>
