<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-COACH FACES CHARGES OF SEX WITH MINOR; ARRAIGNMENT: THE HUNTINGTON BEACH MAN 
AND A STUDENT, 15, FROM THE SCHOOL HE WORKED AT WERE ALLEGEDLY FOUND IN A STATE 
OF UNDRESS IN A CAR. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former assistant baseball coach at a Huntington Beach high school is 
scheduled to be arraigned May 16 on charges of having sex with a minor and 
contributing to her delinquency after police allegedly caught him and a 
15-year-old girl who attends that school partially clad in a car. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley police says an officer found Cory Colbert, 23, with the 
teen-ager early Saturday in a vehicle parked behind a store in the 17200 block 
of Brookhurst Street.At the time, Colbert worked as a coach at Ocean View High 
in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 "The two were (trying to grab) their clothes," police spokesman Dann Bean 
said. Colbert "was arrested and brought to the Police Department that night." 
</P>
<P>
 Colbert of Huntington Beach was released on his own recognizance that same 
night, Bean said. Having sex with a minor is a felony and contributing to a 
minor's delinquency is a misdemeanor, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Colbert has since lost his job as an assistant coach with the boys' varsity 
baseball team, Principal Carla Rush said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Cory Colbert is no longer an employee of the district," said Rush, who is in 
charge of the 2,000-student school that serves Huntington Beach, Westminster, 
and Fountain Valley. She declined further comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Colbert could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
