<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN KILLED, HUSBAND HURT IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Laguna Niguel woman was killed Thursday in a three-car, rush-hour collision 
near the intersection of the San Diego and San Gabriel River freeways, the 
California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Joan Witte, 65, was fatally injured and her husband, Norman Witte, 63, who was 
driving, was seriously injured when their 1988 Pontiac 6000 was struck from 
behind after first colliding with a vehicle in front, CHP Officer Pete 
Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
 A woman in the car that struck the Wittes' vehicle was slightly injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Joan Witte was pronounced dead at the scene. Norman Witte was taken to Long 
Beach Memorial Hospital, where he was reported in fair condition. 
</P>
<P>
 The collision occurred just before 5 p.m. on the southbound San Gabriel River 
Freeway, near Katella Avenue. A 1989 Toyota Tercel in front of the Wittes' 
vehicle slowed suddenly because of congestion at the intersection with the San 
Diego Freeway. The Witte car rear-ended the Tercel, doing minor damage to the 
Toyota. 
</P>
<P>
 As the Toyota pulled over to the center divider, the Wittes' Pontiac was hit 
from behind by a 1979 Toyota Corona. The driver of the Corona, a 28-year-old 
Santa Ana woman, suffered minor injuries. Two children in her car were unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash resulted in a 90-minute SigAlert that backed up traffic to the 
Artesia Freeway, the CHP said. 
</P>
