BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; WHITE SOX RELEASE SAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Steve Sax, bothered by an injured left foot this spring, was put on 
unconditional release waivers by the Chicago White Sox on Thursday. Sax, 34, 
was recalled from his rehabilitation assignment at double-A Birmingham and 
reinstated from the 15-day disabled list before being put on waivers.If he 
clears next week, the White Sox will be responsible for the remainder of his 
$3.1-million salary this year and his $3.1-million salary next season. 
</P>
<P>
 Sax, a five-time All-Star, was put on the disabled list April 1 with a bruised 
left heel. In seven games at Birmingham, he hit .318 with two doubles and one 
run batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Catcher Benito Santiago of the Florida Marlins was suspended for four games 
for "inciting a bench-clearing brawl" but immediately appealed, delaying the 
penalty. Santiago, who also was fined, charged the mound Sunday against the San 
Francisco Giants. . . . Right-hander Tim Worrell of the San Diego Padres was 
put on the 15-day disabled list, retroactive to Tuesday, because of an injured 
right elbow. . . . The Boston Red Sox sent reliever Ricky Trlicek to double-A 
New Britain, Conn., and replaced him with reliever Ken Ryan. 
</P>
