<P>
INVESTOR MAY SEEK CHANGE ON GATEWAY BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBORA VRANA, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An East Coast investor in Gateway Communications Inc., the Irvine marketer of 
computer networking equipment, said it may call for a change in the company's 
board or management. 
</P>
<P>
 Investment Perspectives Advisory Corp., which holds 248,700 Gateway shares, or 
a 4.9% stake, said in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing Thursday that 
it "may desire a change in the present board or the management of the issuer." 
</P>
<P>
 Officials of neither Gateway nor Investment Perspectives could be reached for 
comment. 
</P>
<P>
 For 1993, Gateway posted a loss of $2.27 million, compared to a profit of 
$609,000 for 1992. Revenue declined to $10.4 million from $20.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Investment Perspectives, based in Macungie, Pa., also said it may speak with 
other investors about forming a shareholder group. Steel Partners Ltd., Adage 
Inc., Warren G. Lichtenstein, Jack Howard, Lawrence Butler and Ronald W. Hayes 
have already agreed to participate with Investment Perspectives as a group, 
according to the SEC filing. 
</P>
<P>
 On Thursday, Gateway's shares were up 28 cents to close at an even $1 in 
Nasdaq trading. 
</P>
