<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach High will lose three coaches in boys' and girls' tennis and 
boys' soccer, Athletic Director Dave Van Hoorebeke said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Boys' soccer Coach Randy Chambers is retiring from coaching but will continue 
teaching world history, boys' tennis Coach Tom Harlow is retiring from teaching 
and girls' tennis Coach Lynn Monroe is leaving her walk-on position, Van 
Hoorebeke said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are being accepted through May 6 for all three positions, which 
are for walk-on coaches. For more information, contact Van Hoorebeke at 
536-2514, extension 270. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Todd Belitz of Edison High School has signed a letter of intent to play 
baseball at Washington State, Stan Belitz, his father, said. 
</P>
<P>
 Belitz, who has been on the Charger varsity for four seasons, is 4-0 with a 
2.90 earned-run average this season. Last season he was 6-1 and was named the 
co-player of the year in the Sunset League. 
</P>
<P>
 Belitz was an All-Southern Section Division II selection as a linebacker in 
football. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy catcher Joy Hannifan has signed a letter of intent with the University 
of New Mexico at Albuquerque to play softball next season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley High School's baseball field will be dedicated to Herschel 
Musick before the Falcons' Century League game against Orange on May 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Musick was the school's first baseball coach and returned in 1989 to coach the 
team. He has a career record of 301-264-2. 
</P>
